        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>passenger vehicles [300227816], freewheeled vehicles by form or function [300227810], freewheeled vehicles [300227809], land vehicles by form [300215717], land vehicles [300212968], vehicles (transportation) [300219258], Transportation Vehicles (hierarchy name) [300042929], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Three-wheeled vehicles, particularly of light open framework construction, usually powered by the rider via pedals and cranks, or occasionally by a motor; for similar lightweight manually powered vehicles, but without comfort- or speed-enhancing features, constructed prior to about 1870, prefer "velocipedes." For three-wheeled automobiles, use either "three-wheelers" or "cyclecars."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vehículo de tres ruedas, generalmente de estructura abierta y ligera, que puede estar accionado tanto porenergía, como por el propio conductor o por un pequeño motor. Construido después de 1869. Para vehículos similares, de peso ligero, accionados manualmente, pero sin comodidades o dispositivos de aumento de velocidad, construidos antes de 1870, prefiera "velocípedo”. Para automóviles de tres ruedas, use tanto "triciclo (vehículo)” como "motocarro".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Voertuigen op drie wielen, meestal met een lichte raamwerkconstructie, die ofwel door de berijder zelf of met een klein motortje worden aangedreven en die werden gebouwd na 1869; gebruik 'vélocipèdes' voor soortgelijke lichte, met de hand aangedreven voertuigen zonder comfort- of snelheidsverhogende kenmerken, die werden gebouwd tot ongeveer 1870. Gebruik 'driewielers (auto's)' of 'autoscooters' voor auto's met drie wielen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>車體結構通常為輕型開放式的三輪車，可由駕駛踩動或由小型馬達驅動，約於1869年後發明; 若指稱相似的輕型人力車輛，但不以提升舒適度或速度為特性，於1870年以前製造使用者，較常用 “腳蹬車”一詞。若指稱三輪式的機動車輛，則見“三輪車”或“三輪摩托車”。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
